  "color_desc": {
    "kicker": "The color · in plain words",
    "title_html": "What you're <em>looking</em> at.",
    "prose_paragraphs": [
      "Traditional architectural-shingle brown. Barkwood is a workhorse color on craftsman, traditional, and Tudor-style homes where the roof is meant to grow out of the landscape rather than contrast against it. The granule blend uses warm tobacco and weathered-wood accents to keep the surface visually alive.",
      "The granule blend layers tobacco, amber, and dark walnut granules in a tight rotation. Up close you can see the layering; from the street it reads as one warm color with subtle texture.",
      "Pairs cleanly with brick red, cream, warm white, sage, and natural-wood siding. Slightly less flexible than the gray family on cool or modern color palettes, but unbeatable on traditional elevations."
    ],
